title: Grateful Dead Live at Jai-Alai Fronton on 1974-06-22
lineage: SBD > MR > CASS > DAT > CD > EAC > SHN > DC6 > CD
description:
Set 1: Promised > Bertha > Greatest, Deal, Bobby McGee, Scarlet, Jack Straw, Loose Lucy, Mexicali, Sugaree, Race Is On, Roses, Playin

Set 2: China Cat Sunflower > I Know You Rider, Me & My Uncle, Ship Of Fools, El Paso, Eyes of the World > Wharf Rat > Sugar Magnolia 

Encore: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text: High-Lai ...my heart and mind and soul was absolutely blown away to the point of tears by what must be the best version of Greatest Story ever told I've ever heard...Donna at her best, Jerry on fire, Phil killing it with a hypnotic baseline. My expectations were so low but I was simply amazed by this show. There's something magic about the acoustics in the Jai-Alai Fronton that amplifies the crowd voices between songs and makes the venue feel really small. You can hear so much. Great Bertha, killer Deal. It all rocks. I was not expecting this to be so good. My new favorite show. Get it. Love it. Live it.

Great Concert I went to this concert in 74 and it was awesome! Not sure how 33 years have passed? The Miami Jai-Alai Fronton had great acoustics and I was hooked on the band forever!  Miss hearing more of their music today!
Great concert I went to this concert and it was terrific!  The Jai-Alai Fronton was a great place to see the Dead perform, sat in the 3rd row center stage and I think the tickets were about $20.00
Wow One of the best shows I've heard. Unbelievable Greatest story ever told!

SET LIST ? MAN THAT`S A TOTALY MESSED UP SET LIST, BUT IF YOU CAN GET THROUGH ALL THE TUNING AND FIGURE OUT THE CORRECT SEQUENCE OF SONGS THE MUSIC IS FANTASTIC ! CHECK OUT CHINA CAT & WARF RAT. I`M GIVIN` THIS SHOW 5 STARS !

Me n' Bobby, oh boy! This show is a gem. Jerry was very on this night. One of the more varied and beautiful Bobby McGees, never heard it played that way.

I'd highly recommend the Springfield 1974-06-30 show for more mind blowing mid seventies Dead.

Wonderful indeed! The whole year is one incredible performance but this show stands out among the giants... Jerry is at his greatest, never ceasing to amaze. As others stated this is probably the most amazing Bobby McGee ever and definitively one of the best Greatest Story Ever Told too... the rest of the show is pretty much breathtaking as well!
I attended this one . . .36 years ago The band was great.  The audience was not very attentive or enthusiastic.

extremly underrated while the playing isn't perfect, and obviously the night after is where the big time action is, this show needs way more attention. all the 'little' tunes seem much more energetic and fun than usual. and the china>rider is one of the best i've heard in '74, rivaling the likes of 5/25 and 6/26. the Eyes>Wharf Rat>Sugar Mags is also well jammed with a unique spacey segue from Eyes to wharf rat. like 5/25 and 7/31 this is a great party show... seriously, check it out!
Grate Show! So many great moments…shout out to the 28 minute PITB - psychedelic jazz at its finest!
